# Chat title carries backlog id

When the conversation is about a **tracked backlog item** (GitHub issue / story),
the chat tab title must include that id so the board and the chat stay aligned.

## When

- Starting work on an issue (`#342`, `GH-327`, board card, task-prompt `story_id`)
- Switching focus to a different issue mid-chat
- Starting `/rabbit-loop` or a `task/*` implementation pass tied to an issue

## How (Cursor)

Call MCP **`rename_chat`** (`cursor-app-control`) with a short title:

```text
#<github-issue> · <≤6 word topic>
```

Examples: `#342 · anchor-plan guardrail`, `#267 · work-unit v2 spike`.

Prefer the **GitHub issue number** (`#342`) over the story id (`GH-222`) when
they differ — same rule as PR bodies in `AGENTS.md` (board sync). If only a
story id exists yet, use `GH-NNN · topic` until the issue is filed.

## Do not

- Rename on every trivial turn
- Put private customer names in the title
- Block work if `rename_chat` is unavailable (other editors / headless) — best-effort

Canonical note for the review loop: `docs/skills/rabbit-loop.md` § Chat title.
